How does Vercel calculate usage?

::: {.stack_stack__iZkUS .stack .faq_chevron__UGjZY data-version="v1" style="--stack-flex:initial;--stack-direction:column;--stack-align:center;--stack-justify:center;--stack-padding:0px;--stack-gap:0px"}
![](data:image/svg+xml;base64,)
:::

:::: faq_content__K9TiW
::: {.text_wrapper__i87JK .faq_answer__3LDUk data-version="v1" style="--text-color:var(--ds-gray-900);--text-size:1rem;--text-line-height:1.5rem;--text-letter-spacing:0px;--text-weight:400"}
We calculate the total response size which includes headers along with
the number of bytes in the body. Anything served from our servers from
your project's domain will be counted as bandwidth (including JSON
responses for Serverless Functions).

When it comes to Serverless Functions though, GB-Hrs is calculated by
multiplying the duration that your functions ran for by the amount of
memory that was consumed by them.

To learn more, check out the[Usage
documentation](https://vercel.com/docs/platform/usage).
:::

Potentially. Transfer fees are dependent on the TLD and the domain
renewal fee. The domain-transfer workflow will alert you of fees before
initiating transfer.

Do cached responses affect usage?

::: {.stack_stack__iZkUS .stack .faq_chevron__UGjZY data-version="v1" style="--stack-flex:initial;--stack-direction:column;--stack-align:center;--stack-justify:center;--stack-padding:0px;--stack-gap:0px"}
![](data:image/svg+xml;base64,)
:::

:::: faq_content__K9TiW
::: {.text_wrapper__i87JK .faq_answer__3LDUk data-version="v1" style="--text-color:var(--ds-gray-900);--text-size:1rem;--text-line-height:1.5rem;--text-letter-spacing:0px;--text-weight:400"}
Caching responses can reduce the usage of Vercel Functions.\
[]{.faq_br__B2yMJ}If the function response is
[cached](https://vercel.com/docs/edge-network/caching), it will not run
and incur a Function invocation or any GB/hrs of duration. Any request
made to Vercel will incur an Edge Request. Requests to static assets
incur the same Fast Data Transfer usage if the response is cached or
uncached.\
[]{.faq_br__B2yMJ}Further, Vercel automatically adds etags to all
responses to prevent end users from downloading the same asset many
times. Our Edge Network automatically
[compresses](https://vercel.com/docs/edge-network/compression) responses
to reduce your Fast Data Transfer.
:::

How can I manage my spend?

::: {.stack_stack__iZkUS .stack .faq_chevron__UGjZY data-version="v1" style="--stack-flex:initial;--stack-direction:column;--stack-align:center;--stack-justify:center;--stack-padding:0px;--stack-gap:0px"}
![](data:image/svg+xml;base64,)
:::

:::: faq_content__K9TiW
::: {.text_wrapper__i87JK .faq_answer__3LDUk data-version="v1" style="--text-color:var(--ds-gray-900);--text-size:1rem;--text-line-height:1.5rem;--text-letter-spacing:0px;--text-weight:400"}
We provide customers with tools to observe, control, and alert on their
infrastructure spend with [Spend
Management](https://vercel.com/blog/introducing-spend-management-realtime-usage-alerts-sms-notifications).\
[]{.faq_br__B2yMJ}You can define a spend amount (e.g. \$40) and receive
email, web, and SMS notifications as you reach that amount. When
reaching 100%, you can optionally automatically pause all projects with
a hard limit.\
[]{.faq_br__B2yMJ}Over the past year, we\'ve added features to the
platform based on your feedback to help automatically prevent runaway
spend, including [recursion
protection](https://vercel.com/changelog/automatic-recursion-protection-for-vercel-serverless-functions),
[improved function
defaults](https://vercel.com/changelog/serverless-functions-can-now-run-up-to-5-minutes),
[hard spend
limits](https://vercel.com/changelog/improved-hard-caps-for-spend-management),
[Attack Challenge
Mode](https://vercel.com/changelog/prevent-malicious-traffic-with-attack-challenge-mode-for-vercel-firewall),
and more.
